| style="text-align:center;" colspan="24"| '''Names'''
|- style="text-align:center;"
|  style="width:3%; "|''a''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''be''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''tse''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''de''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''e''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''ef''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''ghe''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''ha''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''i''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''jot/i lung''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''el''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''em''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''en''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''o''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''pe''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''ku''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''er''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''es''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''te''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''u''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''ve''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''iks''||  style="width:3%; text-align:center;"|''tset''
|}

The letters '''k (ka)''', '''w (ve dubel)''', and '''y (ipsilon''' or '''i grec)''' are used only in words borrowed from foreign languages, such as: kilogram, ski, kino, kiosc, kilo, kilowat, Washington, western, stewardess, whisky, happy, or hockey.

Because most Romansh-speaking people are familiar with German spelling, Romansh orthography borrows from German: The "sh" sound, for example, is written in the German fashion, "sch" (see "rumantsch"), not "sc" as in Italian, and <U+00F6> and <U+00FC> are used.

